The paper deals with the security and privacy aspects of USB flash drives, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed framework, MAGNETO, involves analyzing unintentional magnetic emissions, which can also be related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the potential for malicious attacks and the need for protection, which can be categorized under cybercrime (cs.CY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
